						<div class="postbody">Yes, but I can't think of many cases where that would be necessary. Things often happen in the level, and you need to translate that to the screen so that the player can see what's happening, but the opposite should be very rare. In a device with a touch screen you'd do that to check what parts of the level are being touched, but this is obviously not the case of the NES. Would you mind telling us why you need this conversion?</div>

